        <headline>Heat Advisory issued June 21 at 2:28PM EDT until June 24 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...For the first Heat Advisory, heat index values up to 96
degrees expected. For the second Heat Advisory, heat index values
95 to 105 degrees expected.

* WHERE...In Connecticut, Northern Litchfield County. In New York,
Western Schenectady, Montgomery, Southern Fulton, and Southern
Herkimer Counties. In Vermont, Eastern Windham County.

* WHEN...For the first Heat Advisory, from 11 AM to 8 PM EDT Sunday.
For the second Heat Advisory, from 11 AM Monday to 8 PM EDT
Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Hot temperatures and high humidity may cause heat
illnesses.
</description>
        <instruction>Drink plenty of fluids, stay in an air-conditioned room, stay out of
the sun, and check up on relatives and neighbors.</instruction>
